frus:attachment.p:
Recognizing that the territory of West New Guinea
                            will require for some time administrative, technical, and economic
                            assistance and guidance, and in this connection;

Recognizing that the territory of West New Guinea
                            has been the subject of dispute between Indonesia and the
                            Netherlands;

Believing that it would be desirable to establish
                            an international authority to assume responsibility for the
                            administration of the territory;

Affirming the importance of respect for the
                            principle of self-determination as expressed in the Charter of the
                            United Nations;

Considering that the future status of the
                            territory should be determined by its people in accordance with this
                            principle;

list.item:
Requests the Commission: (a)
to inquire into conditions in the territory; (b)
to consider and report on arrangements for bringing the territory during an interim period under the administration of a United Nations Authority established by and operating under the United Nations;

Declares further that this is without
                                prejudice the people’s decision on the ultimate status of the
                                territory;
